A gunman, Charles Carl Roberts IV, killed himself after shooting children in an Amish schoolhouse in Pennsylvania.
The victims were shot in the head and some were taken to the hospital.
Roberts had a history of torment over past events and left notes confessing to molesting young relatives.
The Amish community mourned the loss of innocent lives and reached out to Roberts' family.
Despite the tragedy, neighbors were shocked as Roberts was described as a devoted father and a calm individual.
The incident left the community in disbelief and sorrow.
